Keeping python in a controlled environment can be helpful.
to install this use:

# sudo apt-get install python3-venv

Then to start venv (virtual environment)
# python3 -m venv directory_in_use


(Troubleshoot:
https://stackoverflow.com/questions/45554864/permission-denied-when-activating-venv
)


then activate the environment by:
# source bin/activate

1) sdsd




